title: Taylor on the practice field, despite injury
text:
Taylor on the practice field, despite injury 
Updated: Wednesday, October 14 2015, 07:36 PM EDT 
Buffalo, N.Y. - Tuesday, there were reports that Buffalo Bills quarterback Tyrod Taylor would be out for a few weeks with a knee injury. 
But Wednesday, Coach Rex Ryan said that may not be the case. 
Taylor was out on the practice field Wednesday, but did not appear to be at 100 percent. If he has a sprained knee, it is unlikely he will play against the Bengals. 
Lesean McCoy was also on the practice field, and may be back Sunday. Taylor on the practice field, despite injury Related Stories
